| Method              | Resolves ✅                                                                 | Rejects ❌                                                                 | Return Value 📦                                                                                       | Use Case 🎯                                                                                 |
|---------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Promise.all         | When all promises resolve ✅✅✅                                              | If any promise rejects ❌                                                  | Array [...] of all resolved values (in order)                                                        | Need all results; fail fast if one fails                                                    |
| Promise.allSettled  | When all promises settle (resolve ✅ or reject ❌)                           | Never rejects (always resolves)                                            | Array of { status: "fulfilled", value } or { status: "rejected", reason }                             | Need results of all, regardless of success/failure                                          |
| Promise.race        | As soon as the first promise settles (✅ or ❌)                              | Same — depends on whichever promise settles first                          | Value or error of the first settled promise                                                           | Care only about the fastest result (success or failure)                                     |
| Promise.any         | When the first promise fulfills ✅                                          | Only if all promises reject ❌ (throws AggregateError)                      | Value of the first fulfilled promise                                                                  | Need the first successful result, ignore failures unless all fail                           |



